In [88]:
from math import sin, cos, pi
P = graphs.PetersenGraph()
d = {'#FF0000':[0,5], '#FF9900':[1,6], '#FFFF00':[2,7], '#00FF00':[3,8], '#0000FF':[4,9]}
pos_dict = {}
for i in range(5):
    x = float(cos(pi/2 + ((2*pi)/5)*i))
    y = float(sin(pi/2 + ((2*pi)/5)*i))
    pos_dict[i] = [x,y]

for i in range(5,10):
    x = float(0.5*cos(pi/2 + ((2*pi)/5)*i))
    y = float(0.5*sin(pi/2 + ((2*pi)/5)*i))
    pos_dict[i] = [x,y]

pl = P.graphplot(pos=pos_dict, vertex_colors=d)
pl.show()

In [103]:



    


@interact
def random_walk_in_box(n=(0,500), frame=True):
    point = [0.1,0.1,0.1]
    v = [copy(point)]
    for i in range(n):
        point[0] += random()-0.5
        point[1] += random()-0.5
        point[2] += random()-0.5
        v.append(copy(point))
    show(line3d(v,color='royalblue', width=1),aspect_ratio=[1,1,1],frame=frame)
